An established parent company recently acquired a sports company.

The parent company already had mature data-engineering practices and a structured data platform. In contrast, the newly acquired company stored its sales data in separate source files without:

Standardised data models
Automated data-quality checks
Consistent naming conventions
Historical data management
Analytical fact and dimension tables
A scalable data-processing architecture

The purpose of this project was to integrate the acquired company’s data into a modern and maintainable data platform.
